"{\"uid\": \"kpbs.org-news-national-2024-08-01-golden-again-simone-biles-wins-gymnastics-olympic-individual-all-around-title\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  NPR is in Paris for the 2024 Summer Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 47, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2, \"end\": 5, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.3331225318236187e-11, \"text\": \"NPR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\"}, {\"begin\": 12, \"end\": 17, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.468001884641178e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For more of our coverage from the Games, head toour latest updates.\", \"from\": 48, \"to\": 115, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"PARIS - For the second time in herremarkable career, the peerless gymnast Simone Biles won the Olympic individual all-around final title, only two days afterleading the U.S. women's teamback to the gold medal in the team event.\", \"from\": 119, \"to\": 346, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 193, \"end\": 205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlike many of her other medals over the years, this one did not come easily.\", \"from\": 348, \"to\": 425, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her gold required overcoming an unusually poor performance on the uneven bars that briefly put her into third place behind two strong competitors, includingBrazil's Rebeca Andrade, the gymnast widely considered to be theworld's second best.\", \"from\": 426, \"to\": 666, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 591, \"end\": 605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rebeca Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the setback was not enough to prevent her from winning her sixth Olympic gold and her ninth Olympic medal overall, more than any other U.S. gymnast ever.\", \"from\": 668, \"to\": 825, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have never had an athlete that close, so it definitely put me on my toes.\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 903, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And it brought out the best athlete in myself,\\\" Biles said of Andrade afterward.\", \"from\": 904, \"to\": 984, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 966, \"end\": 973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.7250558113122175e-13, \"text\": \"Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But I knew if I did my work, it would all be fine.\\\"\", \"from\": 985, \"to\": 1037, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles became just the third woman in the history of the Olympics to twice win the individual all-around gold medal, and the first since the 1960s.\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1185, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(The first two-time winner was Larisa Latynina of the Soviet Union, whose nine Olympic golds remain the most ever earned by a gymnast.)\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1321, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1217, \"end\": 1232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Larisa Latynina\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\"}, {\"begin\": 1247, \"end\": 1252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999956981811, \"rank\": 4.290558524102998e-08, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Biles, 27, is the first to win her second eight, rather than four, years after her first.\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1416, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the Tokyo Olympics in 2021, Biles withdrew from the individual all-around afterstruggling with the \\\"twisties\\\"and losing the ability to control her body in mid-air.\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1583, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The intense pressure hadaffected her mental health, Biles said then, and she ultimately took a two-year hiatus from the sport altogether.\", \"from\": 1584, \"to\": 1721, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Leading up to Tokyo, I was so nervous about getting injured physically that I neglected my mental health,\\\" Biles said Thursday.\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1851, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1738, \"end\": 1743, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.7910864767951309, \"rank\": 0.2640842727521534, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Then I was injured, except it was a mental injury.\\\"\", \"from\": 1852, \"to\": 1904, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the time, she thought she might never be able to compete in gymnastics again.\", \"from\": 1905, \"to\": 1985, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But inher return to the sport, she has been dominant, including in this legacy-cementing performance here in Paris.\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 2102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2096, \"end\": 2101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.468001884641178e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Andrade ended the night with silver, to raucous applause from a large Brazilian contingent of fans.\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2203, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2104, \"end\": 2111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.7250558113122175e-13, \"text\": \"Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bronze medal was awarded to the U.S. gymnast Suni Lee, who hadwon the gold medal at the Tokyo Olympicsin 2021 after Biles' withdrawal.\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2342, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2253, \"end\": 2261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Suni Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Thursday, Biles opened the competition in the lead after starting on vault, her best apparatus.\", \"from\": 2344, \"to\": 2442, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles performed her signature Yurchenko double pike and scored a 15.766, jumping out by two-thirds of a point over Andrade.\", \"from\": 2443, \"to\": 2566, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2473, \"end\": 2482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yurchenko_(vault)\", \"score\": 0.9924615128803714, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yurchenko\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yurchenko_(vault)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yurchenko_(vault)\"}, {\"begin\": 2558, \"end\": 2565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.7250558113122175e-13, \"text\": \"Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But her lead disappeared on the very next rotation.\", \"from\": 2568, \"to\": 2619, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On the uneven bars, Biles turned in an unusually poor performance in which her momentum slowed during a swing from high bar to low bar, causing her knees to almost brush the floor.\", \"from\": 2620, \"to\": 2800, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her routine earned just a 13.733, over a half-point lower than her two previous scores on the uneven bars in Paris.\", \"from\": 2801, \"to\": 2916, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2910, \"end\": 2915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.468001884641178e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That moved her into third place, behind both Andrade and Algeria's Kaylia Nemour.\", \"from\": 2917, \"to\": 2998, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2962, \"end\": 2969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.7250558113122175e-13, \"text\": \"Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\"}, {\"begin\": 2974, \"end\": 2981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6494853494330908, \"rank\": 0.5396729420236901, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was a little bit disappointed in my performance on bars.\", \"from\": 3000, \"to\": 3059, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's not usually how I swing,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 3060, \"to\": 3102, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was probably praying to every single god out there, trying to refocus and re-center myself, because that's not the bars I have been training.\\\"\", \"from\": 3103, \"to\": 3248, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A strong performance on the balance beam put Biles back into first place by a slim margin of just 0.166 points over Andrade.\", \"from\": 3250, \"to\": 3374, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3366, \"end\": 3373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.7250558113122175e-13, \"text\": \"Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then came the last rotation of the night: the floor exercise, in which Biles had outscored Andrade two other times in competition so far.\", \"from\": 3376, \"to\": 3513, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3467, \"end\": 3474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.7250558113122175e-13, \"text\": \"Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As every spectator in the 10,100 seats of Bercy Arena watched, Biles dazzled, smiling as she neared the end of her routine as it became clear she had done enough to win gold.\", \"from\": 3514, \"to\": 3688, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3556, \"end\": 3567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bercy Arena\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles walked off the mat holding her two pointer fingers in the air - #1.\", \"from\": 3689, \"to\": 3762, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ultimately, she won by 1.199 points.\", \"from\": 3763, \"to\": 3799, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Simone is the best,\\\" said Andrade, herself the greatest gymnast in the history of her own country, Brazil.\", \"from\": 3801, \"to\": 3908, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3828, \"end\": 3835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.7250558113122175e-13, \"text\": \"Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\"}, {\"begin\": 3901, \"end\": 3907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.5755578185536312, \"rank\": 0.735967569000544, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She called it a \\\"source of pride\\\" to compete alongside Biles.\", \"from\": 3909, \"to\": 3970, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She extracts the best out of me.\", \"from\": 3971, \"to\": 4004, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I hope I do the same out of her,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 4005, \"to\": 4048, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles is set to compete in three more eventsat these Olympics, the individual event finals for vault, balance beam and floor exercise.\", \"from\": 4050, \"to\": 4184, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright 2024 NPR    Loading...  KPBS keeps you informed with local stories you need to know about - with no paywall.\", \"from\": 4186, \"to\": 4304, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Our news is free for everyone because people like you help fund it.\", \"from\": 4305, \"to\": 4372, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Without federal funding, community support is our lifeline.Make a gift to protect the future of KPBS.\", \"from\": 4374, \"to\": 4475, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Donate\", \"from\": 4477, \"to\": 4483, \"entities\": []}]}"